"```sql\nSELECT COUNT(DISTINCT m.molecule_id)\nFROM molecule m\nJOIN atom a ON m.molecule_id = a.molecule_id\nLEFT JOIN bond b ON m.molecule_id = b.molecule_id\nWHERE a.element != 's'\nAND (b.bond_type IS NULL OR b.bond_type != '=');\n```\n\nThis SQL query counts the number of distinct molecules that do not contain the element sulfur ('s') and do not have any double bonds ('='). It uses a LEFT JOIN to ensure that molecules without any bonds are also considered."